Package com.example.chicksevent

Class OrganizerTest

java.lang.Object
com.example.chicksevent.OrganizerTest
public class OrganizerTest extends Object
Unit tests for Organizer.

These tests provide minimal, synchronous verification of the Organizer class, ensuring that no asynchronous Firebase Task behaviour is invoked. Firebase interactions are mocked using Mockito, and FirebaseDatabase.getInstance(String) is statically stubbed to prevent any real network or SDK initialization.

Key Behaviours Verified

  • Organizer ID getters and setters behave consistently
  • isOrganizer() always returns true
  • listEntrants() correctly attaches a ValueEventListener to the expected Realtime Database path for both WAITING and INVITED statuses
  • sendSelectedNotification() correctly delegates to the INVITED branch of sendWaitingListNotification()
  • Overloaded methods that default to WAITING behaviour are verified

All Firebase service references inside Organizer are replaced via reflection to ensure isolated, deterministic test execution with no dependency on network or Android main-thread context.
